{"sequence":17,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T21:13:02.596821920Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-b7e02139","body":"finding_summary: Historical lineage is resolved from the live milestone plan instead of the plan hash/version captured on the task/run.\nseverity: medium\naffected_files: [\"src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs\", \"src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs\"]\nremediation_hint: Use the persisted `plan_hash`/`plan_version` (or persist a bead-title/acceptance snapshot) when filling lineage metadata, and fall back to durable IDs instead of projecting today's plan onto old runs/tasks.\n\nEvidence: `load_task_lineage_detail` always reparses the current `plan.json` (`src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs:1364-1426`), and `read_bead_lineage` / `bead_execution_history` / `list_tasks_for_milestone` do the same (`src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:2065-2218`). Those lookups ignore provenance already stored on `TaskSource` and `TaskRunEntry` (`src/contexts/project_run_record/model.rs:25-41`, `src/contexts/milestone_record/model.rs:364-376`). After any milestone replan or bead rename/removal, these queries will silently relabel historical tasks/runs with the current bead title and acceptance criteria, or return empty lineage details for runs that were valid under the earlier plan version.","dedup_key":"bb70914a92e8ef8aaa535ac79bae7b7317589277479719a34f2271c60ec4417c","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260415203322","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":18,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T21:13:02.606122623Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-cb791f9b","body":"Bug: `load_task_lineage_detail` (project_run_record/service.rs:1364-1427) propagates errors from `milestone_store.read_milestone_record()` and `plan_store.read_plan_json()` via `?`. If a project has a `task_source` pointing to a milestone whose record or plan.json has been deleted or is corrupt, `show_project` returns an error — breaking `project show` and `task show` entirely for that project. Lineage is supplemental display data; it should gracefully degrade to `Ok(None)` when the milestone/plan cannot be loaded. Fix: catch errors from the milestone/plan loading path and return `Ok(None)` instead of propagating. Affected files: src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs (load_task_lineage_detail, lines 1377-1383).","dedup_key":"8dcd7da3fcc03ac40827f8cffc507eb5ed00b8d6ef5f5a5becb92ac48618f355","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6-max","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260415203322","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":19,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T21:13:02.615390886Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-e123f109","body":"Maintainability: `load_task_lineage_detail` (project_run_record/service.rs:1386-1418) reimplements the bead-in-plan lookup logic (workstream iteration, bead ID matching with milestone prefix stripping, acceptance criteria resolution from acceptance_map) that is already factored out as `resolve_bead_plan_details` + `build_bead_lineage_view` in milestone_record/service.rs:2077-2127, and exposed via the public `read_bead_lineage` function. The two implementations could diverge if matching rules change. Fix: replace the body of `load_task_lineage_detail` with a call to `crate::contexts::milestone_record::service::read_bead_lineage(milestone_store, plan_store, base_dir, &milestone_id, &task_source.bead_id)`, which already does the same work. This also simplifies adding the graceful degradation from the first amendment. Affected files: src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs (load_task_lineage_detail).","dedup_key":"1fa3b77780cbb8087940b02c7624cf24644c143ea9542ef6bc546009ca47f754","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6-max","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260415203322","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
