{"sequence":36,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T21:42:37.478171692Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-d0058eb5","body":"finding_summary: Non-milestone `run history --json` responses omit `milestone_id` and `bead_id` entirely instead of emitting explicit `null` values. Both fields are marked with `skip_serializing_if = \"Option::is_none\"` in [src/contexts/project_run_record/queries.rs:292-297] and the CLI's JSON wrapper repeats the omission in [src/cli/run.rs:10764-10769]. That violates the stated backward-compat contract for standalone tasks and prevents JSON consumers from distinguishing \"standalone task\" from \"older binary that never exposed lineage\".\nseverity: medium\naffected_files:\n- src/contexts/project_run_record/queries.rs:292-297\n- src/cli/run.rs:10764-10769\nremediation_hint: Keep the fields optional in Rust, but remove `skip_serializing_if` on the JSON-facing history structs and add a regression test that asserts `\"milestone_id\": null` / `\"bead_id\": null` for a non-milestone project.","dedup_key":"2bc2f4bf88167d62055be5fe8447cc5fb92d03d9ac9dda231b8fc7956c553693","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260415203322","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":37,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T21:42:37.486814183Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-80ff9e53","body":"finding_summary: Milestone-backed task detail queries lose all lineage when `plan.json` is missing or unreadable. `load_task_lineage_detail()` returns `None` as soon as `read_plan_json` or plan deserialization fails in [src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs:1363-1405], even though `read_bead_lineage()` already has a fallback that preserves milestone name/id and bead id without current-plan metadata in [src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:2131-2193]. As a result, `project show` / `task show` make a milestone-linked task indistinguishable from a standalone task after plan loss or corruption, which defeats the new lineage query.\nseverity: medium\naffected_files:\n- src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs:1363-1405\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:2131-2193\nremediation_hint: Stop preemptively returning `None` on missing/corrupt plan artifacts; call `read_bead_lineage()` directly once the milestone exists and let its fallback path return milestone/bead lineage with empty title/acceptance details when plan metadata is unavailable.","dedup_key":"649d83d3485726f409805885b07cde770c99de5f5dc0e4913645d486b574651c","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260415203322","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
